<div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-3">
  <h1 class="mb-0">Live reviews</h1>
  <%= button_to 'Add a review (simulate external change)', live_poke_path,
                class: 'btn btn-success', form: { data: { turbo: true } } %>
</div>
<p class="text-muted">
  This page re-renders itself every 2&nbsp;seconds via a Turbo <strong>morph</strong> refresh.
  Because the gem gives every row a <code>dom_id</code>, only changed rows morph — the rest
  stay put (no flicker, scroll preserved). Click the button (or open this page in a second tab
  and add a review there) and watch a new row appear in place.
</p>
<p class="text-muted small">
  In production you'd drop the poll and add one line to the model
  (<code>broadcasts_refreshes</code>) plus <code>turbo_stream_from :reviews</code> here — the
  markup requirement is identical; the gem already satisfies it.
</p>

<div class="card"><div class="card-body">
  <%= crud_collection @reviews, query: false %>
</div></div>

<script type="module">
  // Poll-based stand-in for ActionCable broadcasting. Same-URL replace visits
  // are treated as refreshes, which morph when turbo-refresh-method=morph.
  setInterval(() => {
    if (!document.hidden && window.Turbo) {
      window.Turbo.visit(window.location.href, { action: "replace" })
    }
  }, 2000)
</script>
